proposed in 1994 

# CSS Pseudo Elements

Add extra styles/content to elements without writing extra markup, directly from CSS

::after
::before

- Add code to your page directly from CSS
- before and after needs *content* css property to work, else wont work.
- Are inline by default

NOTE: PesudoElement on <img> tag do not work, image with src attribute is the content.

## Pseudo Elements Use cases

1. Add * afer labels, or special decorations on lists
2. Control tooltip behaviour, just using CSS, no JS required
3. Add Hello before greeting the user by name
4. Bring in icons before/after the headings, list-items etc.
5. Add open/close quote around text
6. Section seperators
7. Title bars which grows and shrinks with text

